articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel's defence minister ruled out any ceasefire in Lebanon until Israel's goals had been met.
articles.title: Israeli airstrikes hit Beirut suburbs

articles.author: Ted Hesson
articles.description: Donald Trump is expected to take a slew of executive actions on his first day in the White House to ramp up immigration enforcement and roll back President Joe Biden’s flagship legal entry programs, three sources familiar with the matter told Reuters.
articles.title: Trump’s Day One: Deportations, border wall

articles.author: Simon Lewis
articles.description: The outgoing Biden administration's top diplomat, Antony Blinken, heads to Brussels on Tuesday for talks with European allies concerned that President-elect Donald Trump could abandon Ukraine in its war with Russia.
articles.title: Blinken heads to Europe for Ukraine talks ahead of Trump return

articles.author: Andrew Macaskill, Muvija M
articles.description: Welby resigned "in sorrow", saying he had failed to ensure there was a proper investigation into allegations of abuse by a volunteer at Christian summer camps decades ago.
articles.title: Justin Welby resigns as Archbishop of Canterbury over abuse scandal

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A hit-and-run attack at a sports centre in the southern Chinese city of Zhuhai killed 35 people and severely injured 43, local police said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Hit-and-run attack in southern China's Zhuhai kills 35

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, James Mackenzie
articles.description: The Israeli military said it had delivered hundreds of packets of food to cut-off areas of northern Gaza ahead of a U.S. deadline for Israel to get more aid into the Palestinian enclave or face cuts in military assistance.
articles.title: Israel says it is pushing to get aid into Gaza before US deadline as fighting persists

articles.author: Luc Cohen
articles.description: The judge overseeing Donald Trump's criminal hush money case has put off ruling on whether the president-elect's conviction should be thrown out on immunity grounds, enabling prosecutors to weigh next steps following his Nov. 5 election victory.
articles.title: Trump hush money judge delays ruling on immunity following election win

articles.author: Kuba Stezycki, Riham Alkousaa
articles.description: In the seaside town of Amchit, public schools are finally in session again, alongside tens of thousands of internally displaced people who have made some of them a makeshift shelter.
articles.title: Lebanon's public schools reopen amid war and displacement

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Italian Sea Group is not liable in relation to the fatal sinking of Mike Lynch's superyacht, which killed the British tech billionaire and six others, its chief executive said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Italian Sea Group says it is not liable in Mike Lynch yacht sinking

articles.author: Daphne Psaledakis
articles.description: The U.S. on Tuesday imposed sanctions on a commander of Sudan's paramilitary Rapid Support Forces, accusing him of being involved in human rights abuses in West Darfur, as Washington increases pressure over the war in the African nation.
articles.title: US imposes sanctions on Sudanese paramilitary commander
